<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2005-06-01</DATELINE><TITLE>Pulmonary artery thrombosis in a patient with severe acute respiratory syndrome</TITLE><BODY>Severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) is an emerging infectious disease with both pulmonary and extra-pulmonary manifestations. Although coagulation abnormalities are common in these patients, clinically overt thromboembolic events are rarely reported. This report describes the first case of pulmonary artery thrombosis in a patient with laboratory confirmed SARS.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>